{
  "texts": [
    "21 responses were rated about the same, 6 as slightly worse and 1 as worse.",
    "Overall, this shows that Feedback-Edit ITS is effective at 16 improvements vs. 7 degradations.",
    "Analysis of preference justifications reveal that increased response factuality, coherence and conciseness are the main contributors for such improvements.",
    "Inspired by DeepSeek-AI et al. (2025), we investigate whether data generated from the Feedback-Edit system can be used to train models to generate better responses 'zero-shot' (i.e.",
    "without using the scaling system at inference time)."
  ]
}